My entry for the LHC mapping competition, It's not nearly as compleete as I would have liked, and is not really playable (multiplayer) as its only a small section baised on the superconducting magnets at the LHC and only has one spawn for testing.

I kind of rushed this and dont really expect to win anything but It's something. 

If anyone has any problems with the custom texture (although I forgot how to make it shiney), just contact me and I will try fix and re-upload.

Hi all, after two months of waiting the lhc maps finally arrived, this is the second one out and hopefully some more will follow. my map aims tto rebuild the superconducting magnets, which you can see in this picture: SuperconductingMagnets2.jpg. Unfortunately i could not built more of the tunnel, because of the limits hammmer editor and source has, however it still look amazing. Gameplay (this map is for CS:S): the pipe is a bit higher than the the players eyes, so the re wont be any spawnkilling. every player spawns with a pumpgun and a grenade, there will also be grenade pickup spots. there are two stratagies: 1. try to kill the other team with grenades or 2. try to jump and kill the other players before they manage to throw their grenades. you ll need to combine these 2 tactics in order to win. if you run a funserver and you like this map, i hope that you will put it on rotation as it is fully playable, unique and really a lot of fun. if you don't have an own server, but aswell like the map, then you can still vote for me as the winner of the lhc mapping contests as soon as it has finished(30 November). final version: -improoved colorcorrection -added env_lightglow -fixed one fire estinguisher

--------------------------------------------- Last Update: November 30th, 2008. Game: Counter-Strike: Source --------------------------------------------- Hey guys, First off, I would like to thank Terminatrix for starting a contest like this. I was already thinking in make a map of the LHC, but nothing estimulated me until I enter this contest. This is probably the final version of my map. Even it being for CS:S, it only supports 1 player. New sounds were added, as well as new effects and the player is now teleported to a different location. And this time he doesn't die (well, not during the sequence :D). Hope you all enjoy it and that level designers get more interested in joining contests like this. We are not here for points or money. We are here to make fun.

Seeing as i dont know how to contact the original author of this map i hope that he is ok with this upload. I have expanded the usable area in the map to include the tower, the area over the top of the stairs, and the outer edge of the map. I did this expansion of the map at the request of a friend of mine but we most of the clan liked it so i am going to upload it to fpsbanana seeing as i cannot find any other of these maps that has the area expanded. The .nav file was edited so that the bots could get to the top of the map and to the edge, but they never seem to go there so i dont know if i messed something up, or if the .nav just doesnt work the way i would have liked it to.

**UPDATE**
Thanks to Chizbone there is now a .nav for bots, and a radar/overview.
